WHAT YOU SHOULD KNOW BEFORE INSTALLING
---------------------------------------

1. PRIVACY
   Filamind AI runs Large Language Models (LLMs) locally on your Synology NAS.
   Your prompts and conversations never leave your network unless you
   explicitly enable a cloud provider (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google) and choose
   it for a conversation. API keys are stored locally with restrictive
   filesystem permissions.

2. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
   This package bundles the llama.cpp inference engine, distributed under the
   MIT License — https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp.
   On DVA-series NAS it links against NVIDIA CUDA libraries provided by
   Synology's separate NVIDIARuntimeLibrary package (declared as a dependency).

3. NO WARRANTY
   The package is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind, express or
   implied. The author is not liable for any damages, data loss, or system
   instability resulting from its use.

4. GPU SHARING (DVA 3221 only)
   The GPU on DVA-series devices is shared with Synology Surveillance Station
   for camera AI tasks. Running large language models concurrently with active
   camera recording may cause performance contention.

5. MODEL FILES
   Model files (.gguf) you place on your NAS are subject to their own licenses
   (Meta Llama Community License, Mistral License, Apache 2.0, etc.). Please
   comply with each model's license terms — Filamind AI does not redistribute
   any model weights.

